refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public stringDateTime::format stringformat
stringdate_format DateTimeobject stringformat

  &reftitle.examples;



    Displaying the date and time using the procedural form


<?php
date_default_timezone_set('Europe/London');

$datetime = date_create('2008-08-03 14:52:10');
echo date_format($datetime, 'jS, F Y') . "\n";
echo date_format($datetime, DATE_ATOM);
?>







    Displaying the date and time using the object oriented form


<?php
date_default_timezone_set('Europe/London');

$datetime = new DateTime('2008-08-03 14:52:10');
echo $datetime->format('jS, F Y') . "\n";
echo $datetime->format(DATE_ATOM);
?>
?>


    &example.outputs;


3rd, August 2008
2008-08-03T14:52:10+01:00
